President Obama congratulates Malala Yousafzai and Kailash Satyarthi on winning the 2014 Nobel Peace Prize. He praises their work in protecting the rights and freedoms of young people and ensuring they have the opportunity to fulfill their potential. He highlights Malala's bravery in advocating for girls' education and Kailash's efforts to end child labor and slavery. The President emphasizes the shared commitment to justice and the dignity of every girl and boy that Malala and Kailash represent. He calls for a world where all children are treated equally and reiterates the United States' support for those who defend universal human rights.